  <description><![CDATA[<p>Hotel Britannia Excelsior represents good value for money in a great location on <a data-udi="umb://document/7d421e04a79044babf8cafda30e31d4a" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7d421e04a79044babf8cafda30e31d4a}" title="Lake Como">Lake Como</a>. The lake's a stone's throw away and this is where you'll find the hotel's best feature - the floating pool. Take a dip or park yourself on a sun lounger for the day and enjoy drinks from the bar. </p>
<p>The ferry port's not far from the hotel so you've got great links to other resorts on Lake Como. If you fancy a walk, head south towards <a data-udi="umb://document/cdc14b14dbcd46c6bb2d675f73a3a375" href="/{localLink:umb://document/cdc14b14dbcd46c6bb2d675f73a3a375}" title="Tremezzo">Tremezzo</a> where you can stop for a drink and a spot of lunch. It’s about two and a half kilometres each way and the footpath follows the lake. </p>
<p>The hotel dates back to the 19th Century and you'll find traditional furnishings and décor throughout. We've chosen Deluxe Rooms for our guests that offer more space and comfortable amenities. With the platinum all-inclusive upgrade included as standard with Inghams, you'll find you have plenty of choice when it comes to dining. Take advantage of the à la carte restaurants and enjoy authentic pasta dishes in Simply Pasta and uninterrupted lake views at our favourite, the Lido di Cadenabbia Restaurant where they serve an all you can eat Brazilian barbecue (reservations are required for à la carte restaurants). You'll be able to choose a range of local drinks including spirits and tea &amp; coffee at three bars, including those at the sister hotel, <a data-udi="umb://document/607cb51dd2fd45daabd1fe4381945064" href="/{localLink:umb://document/607cb51dd2fd45daabd1fe4381945064}" title="Hotel Bazzoni">Bazzoni</a>. End your evenings in the hotel's main bar, located on the bottom floor, where you can enjoy a drink and live music.</p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 2 hours by coach from Milan Malpensa airport.</p>]]></description>
